      "message": "The code this is replacing looked for \"ANGLE \" (extended here to \"ANGLE (\") before searching for substrings to determine the particular ANGLE backend. I\u0027d rather not change that functionality to just scan for \"Direct3D11\", etc, especially since ANGLE GL backend is dependent on having \"OpenGL\" which seems likely to appear in non-ANGLE renderer strings.\n\nChanged it to return std::tuple\u003cGrGLANGLE, SkString\u003e. WDYT? Seemed preferable than duplicating the header detection.",
